olive oil
2 potato
1 packet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
1 cucumber
½ carrot
1 packet Halloumi
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
drizzle white wine vinegar
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet garlic aioli

• Preheat oven to 240°C/220°C fan-forced.
• Cut potato into bite-sized chunks.
• Place potato, Mumbai spice blend and brown mustard seeds on a lined oven tray. Drizzle with olive oil, toss to coat and spread out evenly.
• Roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• Meanwhile, thinly slice cucumber.
• Grate carrot (see ingredients).
• Cut halloumi into 1cm slices.

• When the potato has 5 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil.
• Cook halloumi, until golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Remove pan from heat, then add sweet chilli sauce, turning halloumi to coat.

• In a large bowl, combine mixed salad leaves, cucumber, carrot and a drizzle of white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season to taste.
• Divide sticky halloumi, spiced potatoes and garden salad between plates.
• Garnish with crushed peanuts and serve with garlic aioli. Enjoy!